feed.title: Butterflies & moths seen at 145 Gibsons Road, Cobains
feed.subtitle: Butterflies and moths seen at 145 Gibsons Road, Cobains, which is a 6 acre property with a growing garden of predominantly Australian native plants. Much of the boundary plantings are of indigenous vegetation.

entry.title: Agrotis munda
entry.content: This moth crawled along the dirt and onto my husband's leather glove while he was gardening.

entry.title: Elhamma australasiae
entry.content: There were two moths asleep on our clothesline box. I had to shift them in order to move the lever. Both moths had the same markings but were different colours. This one was a tan colour, while the other was a dull brownish grey.
